Week 4 - 

Wrapper classes

primitive data type - int, float, char, double, boolean, byte, long, short
                           |
                           |
                  main objective of wrapper class



Integer, Float, Charatcer, Double, Boolean, Byte, Long, Short


1. To wrap primitive into object form so that we can handle primitives also just like objects
2. To define several utility methods which required for primitives

 Integer i = new Integer(10);
 int i = 10;

Double b = new Double(10.5);



Exception Handling
-------------------

Error  java.lang.error

Exception java.lang.exception
 
-> memory leak ( Out of memory error )
->Arthimetic exception
->Indexout bound exception


An unexcepted or unwanted event that disturbs the normal flow of code called exception.




try-catch

try{
  int x = 10
  a = 10/0;   // ->ArithmeticException
}
catch(ArithmeticException e){
 sysout( Do not / with 0 )
}

sysout ( a )   -> 1


throw and throws - Keywords

Throw explicitly throw a single exception

main()
if(age<18){
   throw new ArithmeticException("should be above 18")
}

Types of Exception 

Build - in Excetion

Checked exception - (complie time) force to handle the exception explicitly eg - file not found exception
Unchecked exception - (run time) do not need to handle explicit eg - null pointer exception

User-Defined exception
   -> printStackTrace()
   -> toString()
   -> getMessage()


